# ArcPM — Cursor AI Rules

## Project
AI-powered program management tool for hardware product development (Signal Ring SR1).
Stack: Next.js 14 App Router + Supabase + Anthropic Claude + Tailwind CSS.

## Architecture
- `app/` — Next.js pages and API routes (App Router)
- `components/` — Shared React components
- `lib/` — Supabase client, Anthropic client, TypeScript types, auth context, access control
- `supabase/schema.sql` — Full DB schema, run in Supabase SQL editor

## Key conventions
- All pages are Client Components ('use client') unless they are pure server layouts
- Auth is handled via `lib/AuthContext.tsx` (useAuth hook)
- Role-based access via `lib/useAccess.ts` (useAccess hook)
- 5 user roles: program_ops | npi | hw_quality | marketing | product
- Active program is stored in AuthContext and passed to all API calls as `programId`
- All AI calls go through `app/api/analyze/route.ts` → `lib/anthropic.ts`
- Tailwind utility classes only — no separate CSS files except globals.css
- Use `clsx` for conditional classnames
- Badge classes: badge-blocker, badge-critical, badge-major, badge-minor, badge-go, badge-watch, badge-nogo
- Button classes: btn-primary, btn-secondary
- Card class: card
- Input class: input-base

## Pages still to build
- None — all MVP pages are built. Next: wire Timeline/Risks/Launch/Cert forms to Supabase API routes.

## Documentation
- Project docs live in `docs/` — PRD, Tech Spec, Onboarding Guide, Project Tracker (.docx)
- Source generator: `docs/generate-docs.js` — run `npm run docs:generate` after meaningful changes
- Keep docs in sync when shipping features, changing architecture, or updating roadmap

## DB tables
programs, tracks, risk_items, launch_items, change_log, user_profiles
All tables have program_id FK. RLS enabled — authenticated users can read all, write their own.

## Environment variables needed
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY
